cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.SY 

The paper discusses the regularity theory of optimal transportation maps and its connection to GANs, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new method to tackle mode collapse in GANs, which involves optimization and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of autoencoders (cs.IT) and proposes a new method for approximating the Brenier potential (cs.SY).
